{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881574481,"sessionID":"ses_28535df40ffe95VE8PKIYkSDM5","part":{"id":"prt_d7aca566a001YZUc5Pp1k5mLdy","messageID":"msg_d7aca3d220018Rcu1YF98yQsYS","sessionID":"ses_28535df40ffe95VE8PKIYkSDM5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0b1894d0550c4fd0bae79f5a27a97840","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in the Python SDK for invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router, including session bootstrapping, lifecycle management, and data plane communication.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient initialization\n18: \n19: The system SHALL construct `AgentRuntimeClient` with configurable agent name, namespace, router URL, session options, and timeout settings.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Constructor with all parameters\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", namespace=\"production\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\", verbose=True, session_id=\"pre-existing-session\", timeout=300, connect_timeout=10.0)`\n24: - **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n25: - **THEN** the instance SHALL store `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `verbose`, `router_url`, and `session_id` as provided\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default namespace\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\")`\n30: - **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n31: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"https://router.example.com\"` and `router_url` argument is `None`\n36: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated\n37: - **THEN** `router_url` SHALL be read from `os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")`\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n40: \n41: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n42: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")` is instantiated\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message explaining Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Default timeout values\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\", router_url=\"https://router.example.com\")`\n48: - **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n49: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL default to `120` and `connect_timeout` SHALL default to `5.0`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Session ID bootstrapping\n54: \n55: The system SHALL bootstrap `session_id` via `GET` request to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint when `session_id` is not provided.\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Bootstrap on init when session_id is None\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` during `AgentRuntimeClient` construction\n60: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL instantiate `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` and call `bootstrap_session_id()` which performs `GET {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Extract session header from bootstrap response\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request returns a response\n66: - **WHEN** the response headers are parsed\n67: - **THEN** `session_id` SHALL be extracted from header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Missing session header on bootstrap\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** the bootstrap `GET` request succeeds but response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n72: - **WHEN** the client attempts to extract the session ID\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Reuse provided session_id\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is passed to constructor\n78: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n79: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT call bootstrap and SHALL use the provided `session_id` directly\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Context manager support\n84: \n85: The system SHALL support Python context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient`.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Enter returns self\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` instance `client`\n90: - **WHEN** `client.__enter__()` is called\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Exit closes session\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as `with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`\n96: - **WHEN** the context block exits (normally or by exception)\n97: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `self.close()`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Exit suppresses no exceptions\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs inside the context block\n102: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL return `None` (or `False`) to propagate the exception\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ### Requirement: Invoke method\n108: \n109: The system SHALL provide `invoke()` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime.\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Invoke with payload\n112: \n113: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with valid `session_id`\n114: - **WHEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"hello\"})` is called\n115: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` to `{base_url}` with `json={\"input\": \"hello\"}` and headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Invoke returns response data\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** `invoke()` receives a successful response with JSON body `{\"result\": \"ok\"}`\n120: - **WHEN** the response is processed\n121: - **THEN** `invoke()` SHALL return `response.json()` (the parsed JSON data)\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Invoke without session_id raises\n124: \n125: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with `session_id` set to `None` or empty string\n126: - **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n127: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=30.0)`\n132: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n133: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `30.0` seconds (passed to `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke`)\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Invoke uses default timeout\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** `client.invoke({\"input\": \"test\"})` without `timeout` argument\n138: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n139: - **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `self.timeout` (default `120`)\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient initialization\n144: \n145: The system SHALL construct `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with router URL, namespace, agent name, and timeout configuration.\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Base URL construction\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"https://router.example.com\", namespace=\"prod\", agent_name=\"my-agent\")`\n150: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n151: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\")`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Connection pool configuration\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(router_url=\"...\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"agent\", pool_connections=20, pool_maxsize=20)`\n156: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n157: - **THEN** the HTTP session SHALL use `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=20` and `pool_maxsize=20`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Default pool settings\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without pool arguments\n162: - **WHEN** the HTTP session is created\n163: - **THEN** `pool_connections` SHALL default to `10` and `pool_maxsize` SHALL default to `10`\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: Data plane HTTP requests\n168: \n169: The system SHALL make HTTP requests to the Agent Runtime data plane with proper headers and timeout handling.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Bootstrap GET request\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n174: - **WHEN** the request is made\n175: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {base_url}` with session default headers only (no `Content-Type`)\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Invoke POST request headers\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke(session_id, payload)`\n180: - **WHEN** the request is made\n181: - **THEN** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Invoke POST request body\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, {\"action\": \"run\"})`\n186: - **WHEN** the request is made\n187: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON-serialized payload `{\"action\": \"run\"}`\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Timeout tuple format\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `connect_timeout=5.0` and `timeout=120`\n192: - **WHEN** any request is sent\n193: - **THEN** the `requests` timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple, i.e., `(5.0, 120)`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout=60.0)`\n198: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n199: - **THEN** the read timeout component SHALL be `60.0` while connect timeout remains `self.connect_timeout`\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ### Requirement: Close method\n204: \n205: The system SHALL provide `close()` method to release HTTP resources.\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: Close releases session\n208: \n209: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with an active HTTP session\n210: - **WHEN** `client.close()` is called\n211: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.dp_client.close()` which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Close is idempotent\n214: \n215: - **GIVEN** `close()` has already been called on the client\n216: - **WHEN** `close()` is called again\n217: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT raise an exception\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ### Requirement: Logging\n222: \n223: The system SHALL provide optional verbose logging for debugging.\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Verbose logging disabled by default\n226: \n227: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent\", router_url=\"...\")`\n228: - **WHEN** the client is instantiated\n229: - **THEN** `verbose` SHALL default to `False`\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Logger creation\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated\n234: - **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n235: - **THEN** `self.logger` SHALL be created via `get_logger(__name__)` or similar\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### Requirement: Public API surface\n240: \n241: The system SHALL export `AgentRuntimeClient` from the package root.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Module export\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n246: - **WHEN** the import is executed\n247: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` SHALL be available (listed in `agentcube/__init__.py` `__all__`)\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Data plane client not in public API\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is defined in `agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane`\n252: - **WHEN** checking `agentcube/__init__.py`\n253: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL NOT be in the root `__all__` (accessible via `agentcube.clients` if needed)\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: Error handling\n258: \n259: The system SHALL raise appropriate exceptions for error conditions.\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: ValueError for missing router_url\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent\")` with no `router_url` and no `ROUTER_URL` env var\n264: - **WHEN** instantiation occurs\n265: - **THEN** `ValueError` SHALL be raised with message mentioning Router URL requirement\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: ValueError for missing session header\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** bootstrap response lacks `x-agentcube-session-id`\n270: - **WHEN** extracting session ID\n271: - **THEN** `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` SHALL be raised\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: ValueError for invoke without session\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty\n276: - **WHEN** `invoke()` is called\n277: - **THEN** `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` SHALL be raised\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### Requirement: Header name consistency\n282: \n283: The system SHALL use consistent header names for session identification.\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Session header constant\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n288: - **WHEN** checking class attributes\n289: - **THEN** `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` SHALL be defined as a class constant\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Header name lowercase\n292: \n293: - **GIVEN** session header is set on requests\n294: - **WHEN** the header is added\n295: - **THEN** the header name SHALL be lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` (not `X-AgentCube-Session-Id`)\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Implementation Files\n300: \n301: | File | Purpose |\n302: |------|---------|\n303: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class |\n304: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class |\n305: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Dependencies\n310: \n311: | Package | Purpose |\n312: |---------|---------|\n313: | `requests` | HTTP client |\n314: | `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling (if needed) |\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Validation Checklist\n319: \n320: - [ 